cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for summarizing conversations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses attention-based pointer networks, which are a popular technique in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves training a model to generate summaries, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques for identifying discourse relations (cs.IR) and sequence tagging (cs.SD).
